  calories: 729 kcal
  fat: 10 g
  saturated fat: 5 g
  carbohydrates: 87 g
  protein: 79 g
source: https://www.hellofresh.co.uk/recipes/mushroom-and-pancetta-risotto-56f15b4afd2cb959598b4567
author: HelloFresh
servings: 2
time required: 30 minutes
---

Cut the little root and green leafy bit off the @leek{1}, slice in half lengthways and
chop it into roughly ½cm slices. Chop the @vine tomatoes{2} into roughly 3cm pieces and
cut the @chestnut mushrooms{1} into slices, set aside.

Add @oil{2%tbsp} to a #frying pan{} on medium heat. Once hot add three-quarters of the
leek and fry for about ~{5%minutes} until just softened.

Add the @risotto rice{2} to the pan and cook over medium-low heat for ~{3%minutes},
stirring occasionally.

> If you have some leftover white wine, add 4 tbsp now and let the alcohol bubble off
> for a minute to mellow the flavour!

Add the @vegetable stock pot{1}, @water{300%ml}, @salt{1/2%tsp} and a good grind of
@pepper{}. Bring to a boil, turn down the heat and simmer for ~{20%minutes}, letting
the rice absorb the water, before adding more boiling water, a little at a time, until
the liquid is absorbed and the rice is cooked.

> Boiling water keeps the rice cooking. You will need between 200ml and 300ml of
> additional water to add during the cooking time. We recommend having a pot of water
> boiling so you can easily add it in.

Bring another #pot{} of water to the boil in preparation for the mangetout. Heat
@oil{2%tbsp} to another frying pan and fry the remaining leek, the @British smoked
bacon lardons{3} and the @garlic cloves{2}(chopped) for ~{2-3%minutes} until browned.
Lift out and reserve in a #bowl{}. Add the mushrooms to the same pan and fry for
~{3%minutes} until softened.

Trim off the ends of the @mangetout{1}. Add to the boiling water. Cook for
~{3%minutes}, until just tender, drain.

When the risotto is nearly ready, add the pancetta mix and mushrooms to the cooked rice
and stir together, keeping on low heat until warmed through.

Mix the tomatoes and @baby watercress{1} together to make a side salad. Grate the
@parmesan{100%g} and stir half of it into the risotto along with the mangetout. Serve
your risotto with the rest of the parmesan scattered over the top and the salad on the
side.